---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
import HiddenGem from '../components/HiddenGem.astro'
import WisdomGem from '../components/WisdomGem.astro'
import { SITE } from '../config/site'

const colors = [
  { name: 'Ink', hex: '#06394a', role: 'The midnight ocean — depth, grounding', text: 'light' },
  { name: 'Paper', hex: '#faf5dc', role: 'The calm within — clean surfaces, light', text: 'dark' },
  { name: 'Vermillion', hex: '#c36242', role: 'The Ruby\'s glow — primary actions', text: 'light' },
  { name: 'Gold', hex: '#f8b883', role: 'The emanating light — highlights', text: 'dark' },
  { name: 'Amber', hex: '#d38370', role: 'The warm halo — secondary glow', text: 'dark' },
  { name: 'Slate', hex: '#405969', role: 'The storm clouds — neutral support', text: 'light' },
]

const ecosystem = [
  {
    name: 'tebako',
    url: SITE.github,
    description: 'The main CLI packager. Turns Ruby apps into self-contained executables.',
    category: 'Core',
  },
  {
    name: 'tebako-samples',
    url: SITE.samplesRepo,
    description: 'Ready-to-use build workflows for common packaging scenarios.',
    category: 'Resources',
  },
]
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About — Tebako"
  description="Tebako (手箱) is short for tamatebako (玉手箱), the legendary jewel box. We place your precious Ruby application into a portable, protective box."
>
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden pt-32 pb-16">
    <div class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-0 select-none" aria-hidden="true">
      <span
        class="absolute -right-10 top-10 font-[var(--font-display)] leading-none text-[var(--tb-c-accent)] opacity-[0.04]"
        style="font-size: clamp(16rem, 35vw, 32rem);"
      >
        玉
      </span>
    </div>

    <div class="relative mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6">
      <p class="tb-eyebrow tb-animate-rise">手箱 · ABOUT</p>
      <h1 class="tb-animate-rise tb-delay-1 mt-3">
        A box for your<br /><span class="tb-text-gradient italic">precious code.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="tb-animate-rise tb-delay-2 mt-6 max-w-2xl text-xl leading-relaxed text-[var(--tb-c-text-2)]">
        Tebako is short for <strong class="text-[var(--tb-c-text-1)]">tamatebako</strong> (玉手箱) —
        the legendary jewel box from Japanese folklore. We give the name new life: a portable
        fortress that carries your Ruby application safely to any destination.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 py-16">
    <p class="tb-eyebrow mb-3">THE NAME</p>
    <WisdomGem id="about-name-wisdom" quote="What is precious needs no wrapping — yet wrapping protects it nonetheless." style="display:inline-block; margin-left:0.5rem; vertical-align:middle;" />
    <h2 class="mb-6">Tamatebako — the jewel box.</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4 text-lg leading-relaxed text-[var(--tb-c-text-2)]">
      <p>
        In the folktale of <em>Urashima Tarō</em>, the princess Otohime gives the
        fisherman a beautiful casket as a parting gift. The box — the
        <strong class="text-[var(--tb-c-text-1)]">tamatebako</strong> (玉手箱) — was said
        to contain something precious. Its name breaks down as:
      </p>
      <div class="my-8 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-3">
        <div class="tb-card relative p-6 text-center">
          <p class="font-[var(--font-display)] text-5xl text-[var(--tb-c-accent)]">玉</p>
          <p class="mt-2 font-[var(--font-mono)] text-sm text-[var(--tb-c-text-3)]">tama</p>
          <p class="mt-1 text-sm">jewel, precious stone</p>
          <HiddenGem id="kanji-tama" style="position:absolute; top:0.5rem; right:0.75rem;" />
        </div>
        <div class="tb-card relative p-6 text-center">
          <p class="font-[var(--font-display)] text-5xl text-[var(--tb-c-accent)]">手</p>
          <p class="mt-2 font-[var(--font-mono)] text-sm text-[var(--tb-c-text-3)]">te</p>
          <p class="mt-1 text-sm">hand</p>
          <HiddenGem id="kanji-te" style="position:absolute; top:0.5rem; right:0.75rem;" />
        </div>
        <div class="tb-card relative p-6 text-center">
          <p class="font-[var(--font-display)] text-5xl text-[var(--tb-c-accent)]">箱</p>
          <p class="mt-2 font-[var(--font-mono)] text-sm text-[var(--tb-c-text-3)]">bako (hako)</p>
          <p class="mt-1 text-sm">box, casket</p>
          <HiddenGem id="kanji-bako" style="position:absolute; top:0.5rem; right:0.75rem;" />
        </div>
      </div>
      <p>
        For our project, the metaphor fits perfectly. Your Ruby application is the
        jewel — precious, crafted, irreplaceable. Tebako is the box that carries it:
        <strong class="text-[var(--tb-c-text-1)]">portable, self-contained, and ready to be
        opened anywhere.</strong>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="relative mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 py-16">
    <div class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-0 select-none overflow-hidden rounded-[2rem]" aria-hidden="true">
      <span
        class="absolute -right-8 top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 font-[var(--font-display)] leading-none text-[var(--tb-c-accent)] opacity-[0.03]"
        style="font-size: clamp(16rem, 30vw, 28rem);"
      >
        時
      </span>
    </div>

    <div class="relative">
      <p class="tb-eyebrow mb-3">THE LEGEND</p>
      <h2 class="mb-8">A fisherman, a princess,<br />and three hundred years.</h2>

      <div class="space-y-5 text-lg leading-relaxed text-[var(--tb-c-text-2)]">
        <p>
          Long ago, a fisherman named <strong class="text-[var(--tb-c-text-1)]">Urashima Tarō</strong>
          saved a sea turtle from torment. In gratitude, the turtle carried him beneath the waves
          to the Dragon Palace — <em>龍宮城, Ryūgū-jō</em> — a palace of coral and light at the
          bottom of the sea.
        </p>
        <p>
          There, the princess Otohime welcomed him. For what felt like three days, he feasted,
          watched the dance of fishes, and forgot the world above. When he finally wished to
          return, Otohime gave him a gift: a small casket — the <strong class="text-[var(--tb-c-text-1)]">tamatebako</strong>,
          the jewel box — with a single condition.
        </p>

        <blockquote class="my-8 border-l-[3px] border-[var(--tb-c-accent)] py-2 pl-6 text-xl font-medium not-italic text-[var(--tb-c-text-1)]">
          Do not open it.
        </blockquote>

        <p>
          He returned to the shore and found everything changed. His village was gone.
          His family was gone. <strong class="text-[var(--tb-c-text-1)]">Three hundred years</strong>
          had passed in what felt like three days.
        </p>
        <p>
          In his grief, he opened the box. White smoke billowed forth — and in an instant,
          the years caught up with him. Time, which had been held safely inside the box,
          rushed out all at once.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="relative mt-12 overflow-hidden rounded-[var(--radius-2xl)] p-8 lg:p-10" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-ink), var(--color-ink-deep));">
      <div class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-0 flex items-center justify-center overflow-hidden" aria-hidden="true">
        <span class="font-[var(--font-display)] text-[12rem] leading-none text-[var(--color-gold)] opacity-5">
          永
        </span>
      </div>
      <div class="relative">
        <p class="tb-eyebrow mb-3" style="color: var(--color-gold);">WHAT THE LEGEND TEACHES</p>
        <h3 class="mb-4 text-[var(--color-paper)]">The box held time.</h3>
        <div class="space-y-4 text-[var(--color-mist-pale)]">
          <p>
            The tamatebako held something precious: <strong class="text-[var(--color-paper)]">time itself.</strong>
            The days at the Dragon Palace were not lost — they were preserved, stored safely
            inside the box until it was opened.
          </p>
          <p>
            Tebako does for your code what the tamatebako did for Urashima's time. It preserves
            your application in a state of <strong class="text-[var(--color-paper)]">suspended perfection</strong> —
            frozen at the exact moment of packaging. No dependency rot. No version drift.
            No bit decay. The gems, the runtime, the configuration — all held safe inside the box.
          </p>
          <p>
            When you ship the executable, you hand someone a tamatebako of their own. They
            open it — and your application springs to life, exactly as you intended, exactly
            as you built it. No aging. No erosion. No three hundred years of change between
            your machine and theirs.
          </p>
          <p class="pt-2 text-lg font-medium text-[var(--color-gold)]">
            This is what we mean by timelessness: your code, held outside of time, until the moment it runs.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 py-16">
    <p class="tb-eyebrow mb-3">THE LOGO</p>
    <WisdomGem id="about-logo-wisdom" quote="The Ruby glows because it remembers the hands that shaped it." style="display:inline-block; margin-left:0.5rem; vertical-align:middle;" />
    <h2 class="mb-6">A gravitic cube over the ocean.</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4 text-lg leading-relaxed text-[var(--tb-c-text-2)]">
      <p>
        The Tebako logo is not merely decoration — it is the product, rendered as myth.
        It depicts a transparent cube floating above a stormy ocean at midnight, its edges
        glowing with the warm light of a single Ruby held within.
      </p>
      <p>
        Every element carries meaning:
      </p>
      <ul class="space-y-3">
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="mt-2 h-1.5 w-1.5 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-[var(--tb-c-accent)]"></span>
          <span><strong class="text-[var(--tb-c-text-1)]">Reverse gravity</strong> — the cube pushes away the turbulent waves below, creating a calm, self-contained space within. This is dependency isolation: the chaos of the outside world cannot reach what is inside.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="mt-2 h-1.5 w-1.5 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-[var(--tb-c-accent)]"></span>
          <span><strong class="text-[var(--tb-c-text-1)]">Heavy water walls</strong> — the cube's faces are sheets of dense water that refract light in strange ways. This is the DwarFS virtual filesystem: your entire application tree, compressed and mounted at startup, visible yet protected.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="mt-2 h-1.5 w-1.5 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-[var(--tb-c-accent)]"></span>
          <span><strong class="text-[var(--tb-c-text-1)]">A single Ruby</strong> — at the center floats your application, its warm glow illuminating the darkness. This is the code you wrote, running exactly as you intended, undisturbed by the storm.</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2">
      <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-[var(--radius-2xl)] border border-[var(--tb-c-divider)] p-8 text-center" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-paper-soft), var(--color-paper-warm));">
        <p class="mb-4 font-[var(--font-mono)] text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-[var(--tb-c-text-3)]">On light</p>
        <img src="/branding/logo-ruby.svg" alt="Tebako logo on light background" class="mx-auto max-w-[200px]" loading="lazy" />
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-[var(--tb-c-text-2)]">The transparent background lets the ocean and cube blend with the warm paper surface.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-[var(--radius-2xl)] border border-[var(--tb-c-divider-strong)] p-8 text-center" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-ink), var(--color-ink-deep));">
        <p class="mb-4 font-[var(--font-mono)] text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-[var(--color-mist)]">On dark</p>
        <img src="/branding/logo-ruby.svg" alt="Tebako logo on dark background" class="mx-auto max-w-[200px]" loading="lazy" />
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-[var(--color-mist-pale)]">The midnight ocean becomes the page itself. The Ruby's vermillion glows against the dark.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 py-16">
    <p class="tb-eyebrow mb-3">WHY RUBY</p>
    <h2 class="mb-6">The stone is a Ruby.</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4 text-lg leading-relaxed text-[var(--tb-c-text-2)]">
      <p>
        The gem inside the cube is red because Tebako was born to package <strong class="text-[var(--tb-c-text-1)]">Ruby</strong>.
        The deep vermillion of the stone — <code class="rounded bg-[var(--tb-c-divider)] px-1.5 py-0.5 font-[var(--font-mono)] text-sm text-[var(--tb-c-accent)]">#c36242</code>
        — is the color of a running application, of warmth, of something alive.
      </p>
      <p>
        Ruby is a language built for developer happiness. Tebako extends that promise to
        the end user: the joy of writing Ruby becomes the simplicity of running a single
        file. No gem installs. No version conflicts. No runtime to configure. Just the box,
        opened with a double-click, the jewel glowing inside.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 py-16">
    <p class="tb-eyebrow mb-3">THE COLORS</p>
    <h2 class="mb-6">A palette from midnight and flame.</h2>
    <p class="mb-8 text-lg leading-relaxed text-[var(--tb-c-text-2)]">
      Every color in the Tebako identity is drawn directly from the logo illustration —
      the deep teal-black of the midnight ocean, the warm cream of the calm interior,
      the vermillion of the Ruby's glow.
    </p>
    <div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
      {colors.map((c) => (
        <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-[var(--tb-c-card-border)]">
          <div
            class="flex h-24 items-end p-4"
            style={`background: ${c.hex};`}
          >
            <span
              class="font-[var(--font-mono)] text-sm font-medium"
              style={`color: ${c.text === 'light' ? 'rgba(255,255,255,0.9)' : 'rgba(0,0,0,0.7)'};`}
            >
              {c.hex}
            </span>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-[var(--tb-c-card)] p-4">
            <p class="font-[var(--font-display)] text-lg font-medium text-[var(--tb-c-text-1)]">{c.name}</p>
            <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-[var(--tb-c-text-3)]">{c.role}</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 py-16">
    <p class="tb-eyebrow mb-3">HOW IT WORKS</p>
    <h2 class="mb-6">The box, opened.</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4 text-lg leading-relaxed text-[var(--tb-c-text-2)]">
      <p>
        Beneath the poetry is solid engineering. Tebako uses
        <strong class="text-[var(--tb-c-text-1)]">DwarFS</strong> — a fast, high-compression
        read-only filesystem — to pack your entire application tree into a single mountable
        image. At runtime, this image is mounted and your application starts as if it were
        running in its original directory structure.
      </p>
      <p>
        The Ruby runtime itself is patched and embedded, so the executable is truly
        self-contained. Native C extensions, gem dependencies, configuration files —
        everything travels inside the box.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="mt-8 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-3">
      <div class="tb-card p-6">
        <p class="font-[var(--font-mono)] text-3xl text-[var(--tb-c-accent)]">01</p>
        <h3 class="mt-2 font-[var(--font-display)] text-lg font-medium">Press</h3>
        <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-[var(--tb-c-text-2)]">A single command packages your app.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tb-card p-6">
        <p class="font-[var(--font-mono)] text-3xl text-[var(--tb-c-accent)]">02</p>
        <h3 class="mt-2 font-[var(--font-display)] text-lg font-medium">Mount</h3>
        <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-[var(--tb-c-text-2)]">At runtime, DwarFS mounts the image.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tb-card p-6">
        <p class="font-[var(--font-mono)] text-3xl text-[var(--tb-c-accent)]">03</p>
        <h3 class="mt-2 font-[var(--font-display)] text-lg font-medium">Run</h3>
        <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-[var(--tb-c-text-2)]">Your Ruby app executes — anywhere.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 py-16">
    <p class="tb-eyebrow mb-3">THE ECOSYSTEM</p>
    <h2 class="mb-6">Open source, built together.</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4">
      {ecosystem.map((project) => (
        <a
          href={project.url}
          class="tb-card group flex items-center justify-between gap-4 p-6"
        >
          <div>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
              <h3 class="font-[var(--font-display)] text-xl font-medium text-[var(--tb-c-text-1)] group-hover:text-[var(--tb-c-accent)]">
                {project.name}
              </h3>
              <span class="rounded-full bg-[var(--tb-c-divider)] px-2.5 py-0.5 font-[var(--font-mono)] text-xs text-[var(--tb-c-text-3)]">
                {project.category}
              </span>
            </div>
            <p class="mt-1 text-[var(--tb-c-text-2)]">{project.description}</p>
          </div>
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" class="h-5 w-5 flex-shrink-0 text-[var(--tb-c-text-3)] transition-all group-hover:translate-x-1 group-hover:text-[var(--tb-c-accent)]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true">
            <path d="M5 12h14M13 6l6 6-6 6" />
          </svg>
        </a>
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 py-16">
    <div
      class="relative overflow-hidden rounded-[2rem] border border-[var(--tb-c-divider-strong)] p-12 text-center"
      style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-ink), var(--color-ink-deep));"
    >
      <span
        class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-0 flex items-center justify-center font-[var(--font-display)] text-[18rem] leading-none text-[var(--color-gold)] opacity-5"
        aria-hidden="true"
      >
        玉
      </span>
      <div class="relative">
        <h2 class="text-[var(--color-paper)]">Ready to open<br />the box?</h2>
        <p class="mx-auto mt-4 max-w-md text-lg text-[var(--color-mist-pale)]">
          Package your first Ruby application in minutes.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-4">
          <a href={SITE.docs} class="tb-btn tb-btn-primary">Get started</a>
          <a
            href={SITE.github}
            class="tb-btn tb-btn-ghost"
            style="color: var(--color-paper); border-color: rgba(245, 237, 208, 0.3);"
          >
            View on GitHub
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
